{
  "question_text": "<h3>Longest Palindromic Substring</h3><p>Given a string <code>s</code>, return the longest palindromic substring in <code>s</code>.</p>",
  "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "A single string `s`.",
  "output_format": "A single string representing the substring.",
  "constraints": [
    "1 <= s.length <= 1000",
    "s consist of only digits and English letters."
  ],
  "explanation": "We iteratively traverse throughout every single character bounds in the parent string. By utilizing the \"Expand Around Center\", we explicitly radiate symmetrically outwards from `i` treating it inherently as both a single-character pivot origin and a double-character block origin respectively checking strict exact-match mirroring mappings directly without auxiliary storage layers optimizing towards O(N^2) max bound.",
  "answer": "def solve(s):\n    res = \"\"\n    resLen = 0\n    for i in range(len(s)):\n        l, r = i, i\n        while l >= 0 and r < len(s) and s[l] == s[r]:\n            if (r - l + 1) > resLen:\n                res = s[l:r+1]\n                resLen = r - l + 1\n            l -= 1\n            r += 1\n        l, r = i, i + 1\n        while l >= 0 and r < len(s) and s[l] == s[r]:\n            if (r - l + 1) > resLen:\n                res = s[l:r+1]\n                resLen = r - l + 1\n            l -= 1\n            r += 1\n    return res",
